fix(rust/bash): Hybrid comsub parser with full recursive parse validation

Replace the character-level comsub scanner with a hybrid approach
inspired by C bash's parse_comsub/xparse_dolparen:

Phase 1: Character-level scan (find_comsub_boundary) finds the $(...)
boundary handling quotes, case/esac, heredocs, nested $(), aliases,
and } inside ${...} contexts.

Phase 2: Full recursive parse (validate_comsub_text) validates the
bounded text, catching errors like:
- Misplaced reserved words in case bodies (done, fi, then, etc.)
- Reserved word "in" at command position
- Incomplete compound commands
- Alias expansion in comsub validation

Key improvements:
- Comsub syntax errors detected at parse time (not execution time)
- Proper "while looking for matching ')'" suffix in error messages
- Syntax errors in comsubs halt script execution like C bash
- COMSUB: error prefix for proper error routing
- SyntaxError word parts propagated through parser via take_word_checked
- Lexer comsub_eof mode with paren_depth tracking for nested contexts